Chermoula

1 tbsp grated ginger
1/2 c chopped flat leaf parsley
1/3 c chopped cilantro
zest and juice of 1 lemon
1 tbsp minced jalapeno
pinch saffron (optional)
1/2 c evoo
salt to taste

Using a mortar and pestle, or in the bowl of a food processor, pound or pulse the ginger into a paste. Add the parsley, cilantro, lemon zest, jalapeno, saffron, and mash or pulse to combine. Slowly pour the oil in a steady stream while blending to form an emulsion. Transfer to a bowl and stir in the lemon juice. Season with salt, cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hrs before serving.
